articles.description: Brandon Better scored a career-high 27 points, Jadon Cohee added 20 and No. 10 seed Southern Utah upset second-seeded Idaho 92-78 on Thursday night in a Big Sky Conference Tournament quarterfinal.
articles.headline: Southern Utah upsets Idaho 92-78 in Big Sky quarterfinal

articles.description: There are no guarantees in March, so UCLA will continue to try to keep winning as it pertains to the NCAA Tournament.
articles.headline: UCLA aims to beat No. 14 Arizona again

articles.description: West Virginia head coach Bob Huggins says his team was able to overcome a slow start by focusing on better ball movement and off-ball cuts.
articles.headline: Huggins credits fundamentals for first-half run

images.caption: West Virginia head coach Bob Huggins says his team was able to overcome a slow start by focusing on better ball movement and off-ball cuts.

articles.description: No. 11 Wichita State ended the regular season on a sour note, losing at home to No. 8 Cincinnati on Sunday. It cost the Shockers a share of the American Athletic Conference title in their first year in the league.
articles.headline: No. 11 Wichita State ready for Temple in AAC Tournament

articles.description: Miami coach Jim Larranaga wants his team to stop making uncharacteristic mistakes and calm down in the second half.
articles.headline: Larranaga says Miami made too many mistakes in first half

articles.description: C.J. Burks scored 29 points, Ajdin Penava posted a double-double and No. 4 seed Marshall beat fifth-seeded UT San Antonio 95-81 in a Conference USA Conference quarterfinal game Thursday night.
articles.headline: Burks' 29 points leads Marshall past UTSA in C-USA tourney
